{#- ``cell`` sanitises a value for inclusion in a single markdown table
    cell. Three problems in raw log fields:
      1. A literal ``|`` collapses the cell — subsequent text reads as
         the next column. Escape with ``\|`` per CommonMark.
      2. A literal ``\n`` (multi-line stack traces, Go panics) starts a
         new row mid-record. Replace with a space so the message stays
         on one logical line and trace_id substrings survive.
      3. A literal ``\r`` (CRLF-emitting containers) leaves a stray
         carriage return that some renderers reposition the cursor on;
         strip outright.
    Order matters: newline normalisation before pipe-escape would also
    work, but doing pipe first means a message like ``a|b\nc`` becomes
    ``a\|b c`` rather than ``a\|b\nc`` getting double-traversed.
    ``(v or '')`` coalesces None — the observer's ComponentLogEntry has
    every field optional, so any of the three columns can be None on
    malformed indexer output. -#}
{%- macro cell(v) -%}
{{- (v or '') | replace('|', '\|') | replace('\n', ' ') | replace('\r', '') -}}
{%- endmacro -%}
